      "SummaryText": "EQUISTAR CHEMICALS, LP  BAYPORT PLANT\r\n\t\t\tEPA RISK MANAGEMENT PLAN\r\nINTRODUCTION\r\n The  Federal Clean Air Act (CAA) Amendments of 1990, section 112(r), mandated EPA to establish a program for the industry to  follow  in  prevention  of serious  accidental  chemical releases  that  may  potentially affect the  public  health, welfare, and the environment.\r\nThis EPA program addresses the following:\r\n1)\tRisk  Management Plan - It summarizes the overall  risk\r\nmanagement  program and was initially submitted  to  EPA  by 6/21/99, and available to state and local emergency planning officials and the public.\r\n2)  Hazard Assessment.\r\n3)  Accident Prevention program for a Level 3 facility\r\n4)\tEmergency Response program.\r\n40 CFR 68.155 (a)\r\nACCIDENTAL   RELEASE\tPREVENTION  AND  EMERGENCY   RESPONSE\r\nPOLICIES\r\nThe  following  represents  Equistar Chemicals' Policy  Statement on Health, Safety and the Environment:\r\nEquistar Chemicals is committed to manage its activities in such  a  way as to take foremost account of:\r\nA\u00bf     The  health  and  safety of employees,  contractors,\r\n\t\tcustomers and the public.\r\nA\u00bf\t\tThe protection of the environment.\r\nIt is committed to implement the Responsible Care program of the Chemical Industry.\r\nIn carrying out this policy Equistar Chemicals shall:\r\nA\u00bf    Manage HSE Matters as a critical business activity.\r\nA\u00bf\t\tPromote good health practices, and ensure a healthy\r\nworking environment for employees and contractors.\r\nA\u00bf\t\tMaintain a systematic approach to HSE by implementing\r\nan HSE Management System designed to ensure compliance with law, achieve continual performance improvement and prevention of pollution.\r\nA\u00bf\t\tIncorporate health, safety and environmental\r\nassessments into all strategic decisions such as acquiring or disposing of assets, and modifying plants or procedures. A\u00bf\t\tEnsure the responsible and efficient use of materials\r\nand energy through innovative technology, education, and good management practices.\r\nA\u00bf\t\tPromote a positive culture"
    },
