      "SummaryText": "d product  goes  to  an extruder  for  pelletizing with some  being  loaded  out  as flake.\r\nThe polymer is used as a raw material by other companies  to produce  vehicle  bumpers, home sidings,  medical  syringes, shatter-proof packaging that is child safe, bicycle helmets, food  plastic  wrap & containers, disposable  baby  diapers, yarn for clothes and carpets, and tools.\r\nThe Equistar Chemicals Bayport plant employs 182  people. The plant property  is approximately 213 acres, 165 of which  is  used for the manufacturing activities.\r\n40 CFR\t68.155(c)\r\nGENERAL  ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM AND CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS\r\nProcesses at Equistar Chemicals are covered by the OSHA PSM rule and the EPA  RMP  rule.   Equistar Chemicals has written procedures  to  verify, manage,  and  audit  ongoing  compliance.   This  prevention program  contains a unit description and affected Chemicals ; process   safety   information;  process  hazard   analysis; standard  operating procedures; employee training  programs; maintenance,  including equipment inspection and  mechanical integrity;   management  of  changes;   pre-startup   safety reviews; internal compliance audits; incident investigation; employee participation; safety (including hot) work permits; contractor safety and evaluations.  Additionally, Equistar Chemicals has developed and implements a Safety Design Criteria (based  on good engineering practices) which is utilized in the design, construction,  production, & preventive maintenance  of  our processes & safe operations.\r\n40 CFR\t68.155 (d)\r\n 5-YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY\r\nThere  has been no accidental release of a covered  chemical\r\nfrom  a  covered  process within the last  five  years  that resulted in deaths, injuries, or significant property damage on-site  or  off-site, and no deaths, injuries, evacuations, sheltering  in  place,  property  damage,  or  environmental damage.\r\n40 CFR\t68.155 (e)\r\nEMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM\r\nEquistar Chemicals has e"
